message.content:
There are several verb tenses in English, including:

1. Present simple (e.g., "I go to the store")
2. Present continuous (e.g., "I am going to the store")
3. Present perfect (e.g., "I have gone to the store")
4. Past simple (e.g., "I went to the store")
5. Past continuous (e.g., "I was going to the store")
6. Past perfect (e.g., "I had gone to the store")
7. Future simple (e.g., "I will go to the store")
8. Future continuous (e.g., "I will be going to the store")
9. Future perfect (e.g., "I will have gone to the store")

It's worth noting that there are also other verb forms, such as the imperative, infinitive, and gerund, which can function like verbs but do not follow the same tense patterns as regular verbs.
